      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 3897: validate() only verifies the HEAD commit and the objects reachable from HEAD\u0027s tree, but it does not verify parent commits/history. Conversation operations such as log traversal, merge-base checks, validClone(), or signature validation can still fail or loop if a pack containing older commits is missing while HEAD and its current tree remain present. Walk the commit graph from HEAD and verify each commit and its tree, or run an equivalent libgit2 object connectivity check before considering the repository valid.\n```suggestion\n// Pseudocode: walk all commits reachable from HEAD and validate each tree.\ngit_revwalk* walk \u003d nullptr;\nif (git_revwalk_new(\u0026walk, repo.get()) \u003c 0)\n    return false;\nGitRevwalk revwalk {walk};\nif (git_revwalk_push_head(revwalk.get()) \u003c 0)\n    return false;\n\ngit_oid commitOid;\nwhile (git_revwalk_next(\u0026commitOid, revwalk.get()) \u003d\u003d 0) {\n    git_commit* commitPtr \u003d nullptr;\n    if (git_commit_lookup(\u0026commitPtr, repo.get(), \u0026commitOid) \u003c 0)\n        return false;\n    GitCommit commit {commitPtr};\n    git_tree* treePtr \u003d nullptr;\n    if (git_commit_tree(\u0026treePtr, commit.get()) \u003c 0)\n        return false;\n    GitTree tree {treePtr};\n    if (git_tree_walk(tree.get(), GIT_TREEWALK_PRE, checkEntry, repo.get()) \u003c 0)\n        return false;\n}\n```",
